how to run a backend using nodeJs, mongodb and express

Install Node.js - If you haven't already, download and install Node.js from the official website: https://nodejs.org/. This will also install npm (Node Package Manager), which you'll use to manage your project dependencies.
You'll need to install Express and Mongoose (a MongoDB object modeling tool) as dependencies for your project - npm install express mongoose
Run your server - node server.js
